<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    Natural/existing heirarchy at toplevel?
From:       <a href="?a=95837693400003&r=1&w=2">Rem () IMSSS</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198511">1985-11-04 15:34:00</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426605&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426605&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Alternatives to the geographical/political heirarchy (where IMSSS would be
located in PINE.STANFORD.PALOALTO.SCLARA.CA.USA.EARTH) might include any
large group of organizations where somebody has already taken the burden
of registering the names and identities of organizations and is now
willing to extend that registry to include our domain system. Examples
that come to mind are: Thomas (registry of manufacturing and other large
companies), executive department (knows about military and all other
bureaucratic entities under it), FAA (commercial and private airliners
who might have mobile network nodes), also somebody probably maintains
a master list of educational institutions whose degrees and partial credit
are acceptable to other schools, ...
Have any of these existing registries been contacted regarding the question
of whether they would be willing to maintain a network-accessibl listing
of their name/organization entries, which a nameserver could then use
to initialize its database and later maintain most of it automatically?
